Clear cell renal cell carcinoma (ccRCC) is the most common histological subtype 
of renal cell carcinoma. The prognosis for patients with ccRCC has improved over 
recent years with the use of combination therapies with an anti-programmed 
death-1 (PD-1) backbone. This has enhanced the quality of life and life 
expectancy of patients with this disease. Unfortunately, not all patients 
benefit; eventually, most patients will develop resistance to therapy and 
progress. Recent molecular, biochemical, and immunological research has 
